The South African Communist Party has slammed ANC Secretary General, Fikile Mbalula. It comes after Mbalula's remarks about a possible cabinet reshuffle by President Cyril Ramaphosa. To discuss the party's plans for the year, SACP General Secretary, Solly Mapaila. #DStv403  JOHANNESBURG - ANC Secretary General Fikile Mbalula has no mandate to speak about a Cabinet reshuffle without consulting the tripartite alliance. That's according to SACP General Secretary, Solly Mapaila. Cabinet Reshuffle | Relax and watch this space - Ramaphosa Speaking at the 27th anniversary of the death of struggle stalwart Joe Slovo, Mapaila says the utterances are disrespectful and will hamper the alliance's reconfiguration. ANC Secretary General Fikile Mbalula told the media that conversations will start in the next two weeks. 